        	<h4>Accommodations:</h4>
			<p>The bride and groom will likely be staying on the South Coast of the island at Southern Palms (Bougainvillea has recently informed us that they are doing renovations). We may move to another hotel the night of the wedding.</p>
			<p class="detailsPagesImages"><img src="http://juliaandandy.com/images/us.png" alt="" /><br /><span class="caption">In Northern Barbados, May 2012</span></p>
			<p>It’s a relatively small island geographically, but the roads are definitely not on a grid system (as we are used to here in the US) and getting around from one point in the island to another can take a bit of time (from the south of the island to the top of the island by car takes about an hour). Given this, we recommend that you stay in or close to the parish (like a county) of Christ Church. You can see it on a <a href="http://www.accessbarbados.com/barbados_parishes.php">map here</a> (for your reference, Fisher Pond is in St. John).</p>

<p><strong>Here are a few recommendations in the area:</strong>
