  <h4>Getting There:</h4>
  <p>Fly to Bridgetown International (BGI). Carriers include: Jet Blue, American Airlines, Britsh Airways, Virgin Atlantic, Air Canada, WestJet, US Airways, American Eagle, Caribbean Airways, LIAT and a number of charter airlines. <span class="red">NOTE:</span> American Airlines will give our guests a 5% discount off the lowest applicable published air fare using the Promotion Code: <strong>8292BX</strong>.The discount will be valid from Sep 22- Oct 6, 2012 for travel to Barbados (BGI).</p>   
  <h4>Getting Around:</h4>
  <p>Public transport is <strong>solid</strong> and taxis abound (in the busy areas), but consider renting a car if you want to have the freedom to explore the island (Note: We rented a car for 3 days and it cost about $200US. Buses/Vans are $1 US/$2 Bajan). Roads are generally narrow - at times ridiculously so - and you'll have to get used to driving on the other side of the road, but for us, it was worth it. If you do rent a car<span class="red">*</span>, pay the extra few bucks for GPS.</p>
  <p>Note: We will provide transportation to/from the wedding location from/to your hotels.</p>  
